<hr size="1" noshade="noshade" /><a name="39"></a>
<div class="a2">To: <b>mazda77</b></div>
<div class="b2">
    <p>It was a joy to read your post. I often reminisce about my days is scouting and fondly remember being elected to the Order of the Arrow. My time spanned between 1957 and 1966 but I could see some not so good changes taking place back then.</p>
<p>Our entire troop would summer camp at Pine Grove Furnace in PA and one year we shared the camp ground with another troop. That troop&#8217;s leaders did all the cooking, cleaning, camp setup and routine chores and the boys were pretty much left with a lot a spare time they wasted on vandalism and malicious mischief. I never made Eagle but this other troop had more than you could shake a stick at and considering their lack camping skills, it was puzzling to me at that time.</p>
<p>This latest move by BSA is a complete betrayal of everything Lord Baden-Powell tried to impart into scouting. How can anyone take the Scout Oath and Laws seriously anymore? It is truly a sad moment.</p>

<br clear="all"></div>
